column7:
Everything that you state as fears under a conservative administration are the exact fears, in reverse, that I had under Obama and I feel we suffered under the Obama administration: 

We placated our enemies;
We abandoned our friends;
We turned a blind eye and a deaf ear to the suffering of the world;
We created the Syrian humanitarian crisis through inaction and false redlines;
We showed the world that they could push us around and treat their people and ours like chattel; 
We empowered mad men in Iran, North Korea and elsewhere;
We fostered and encouraged the current nuclear hostilities with Iran and North Korea with our do nothing foreign policies;
We passed a worthless care act;
We had SJWs directing attacks against conservatives;
We had PC culture running rampant and destroying our national identity;
We pushed the false BLM narrative;
We allowed enemies from without, like Soros, to dictate policy both at home and abroad, etc.  

Your fears are yet to materialize.  The president is just starting to allay mine.
